  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I be myself? No matter where I am or how I am, I just can't be myself and I get very nervous",
  "response": "Feeling nervous and struggling to be yourself is something many people experience, so you're not alone in this. Here are some strategies that may help you feel more comfortable being yourself:\n\n1. **Self-Awareness**: Take some time to reflect on who you really are. What are your values, interests, and passions? Understanding yourself better can help you feel more confident in expressing that self to others.\n\n2. **Practice Self-Compassion**: It's important to be kind to yourself. Recognize that everyone has insecurities and that it's okay to feel nervous. Treat yourself as you would treat a friend who is feeling anxious.\n\n3. **Start Small**: Begin by expressing yourself in low-stakes situations. This could be sharing your opinion in a small group or wearing something that reflects your style. Gradually build your confidence in more challenging situations.\n\n4. **Connect with Supportive People**: Surround yourself with people who accept and appreciate you for who you are. Positive relationships can help you feel more at ease and encourage you to be authentic.\n\n5. **Challenge Negative Thoughts**: Notice when negative self-talk arises and try to challenge it. Ask yourself if those thoughts are really true and consider more positive, realistic alternatives.\n\n6. **Mindfulness and Breathing Exercises**: Practicing mindfulness can help center you in the present moment. Breathing exercises can reduce anxiety and help you feel more grounded when you\u2019re feeling nervous.\n\n7. **Set Realistic Expectations**: Understand that it's okay to not be perfect. Being yourself doesn't mean you have to please everyone or perform in a certain way. \n\n8. **Embrace Vulnerability**: Being open about your feelings can be scary, but it can also strengthen your connections with others. Vulnerability can lead to deeper, more authentic relationships.\n\n9. **Seek Professional Help**: If your feelings of nervousness are overwhelming, consider talking to a therapist or counselor. They can provide you with coping strategies and support tailored to your needs.\n\n10. **Celebrate Your Uniqueness**: Remember that your individuality is something to be celebrated. Engage in activities that highlight your strengths and interests, allowing you to embrace who you are fully.\n\nBeing yourself is a journey, and it takes time to feel comfortable and confident. Be patient with yourself and take it one step at a time.",
